# Manual HTTP probes for the library server.
#
# How to use:
#   1. Start the server with `task run`.
#   2. Open this file in JetBrains GoLand/IntelliJ or in VSCode with the
#      REST Client extension installed.
#   3. Click the gutter icon next to a request to send it.
#
# The `{{baseUrl}}` variable resolves from the `@baseUrl` line below.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### GET {{baseUrl}}/healthz — Phase 1 (liveness probe)
# Expected: status 200, body {"status":"ok"}
GET {{baseUrl}}/healthz

### GET {{baseUrl}}/does-not-exist — Phase 1 (404 fallthrough)
# Expected: status 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/does-not-exist

### POST {{baseUrl}}/members — Phase 2 (membership)
# Activate when Phase 2 lands. Until then this block is inert.
# POST {{baseUrl}}/members
# Content-Type: application/json
#
# {
#   "name": "Ada Lovelace",
#   "email": "ada@example.com"
# }

### POST {{baseUrl}}/loans — Phase 3 (lending)
# Activate when Phase 3 lands. Until then this block is inert.
# POST {{baseUrl}}/loans
# Content-Type: application/json
#
# {
#   "memberId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
#   "bookId":   "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"
# }

### POST {{baseUrl}}/chat — Phase 5 (chat, SSE)
# Activate when Phase 5 lands. Until then this block is inert.
# Response will be a text/event-stream — use REST Client's SSE support.
# POST {{baseUrl}}/chat
# Content-Type: application/json
# Accept: text/event-stream
#
# {
#   "message": "Recommend a book about distributed systems."
# }
